# match is Strict

`match` uses `===`, so `"1"` does not match `1`.

```php
$value = "1";

$result = match ($value) {
    1 => 'integer',
    "1" => 'string',
};
// result is 'string'
```

This avoids the type juggling surprises of `switch`.
